Four armed men robbed a bank manager at knifepoint on Begur Road in Hulimavu on Saturday night.The victim, Dilip Kumar Pandey, branch manager of Canara Bank near Town Hall, was returning home on his motorbike after work. After reaching Begur Elenahalli road, he slowed down as he approached a speed breaker.Thatâ€™s when four men in two motorbikes waylaid him.The gang threatened Mr. Pandey and snatched away his wallet containing Rs. 13,000 in cash, a credit and a debit card.The gang also took away his mobile phone and sped away. Mr. Pandey has filed a complaint.